text: Methenmadinone, also known as deacetylsuperlutin or as 16-methylene-6-dehydro-17α-hydroxyprogesterone, is a pregnane steroid which was never marketed. It is a parent compound of methenmadinone acetate (the C17α acetate ester), melengestrol (the C6 methyl derivative), and chlormethenmadinone (the C6 chloro derivative). ==References== Category:Abandoned drugs Category:Tertiary alcohols Category:Diketones Category:Pregnanes Category:Progestogens
title: Methenmadinone
